<html
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xml:lang="en"
    lang="en"
    metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
    i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
    <div tal:replace="structure view/viewsPortlet" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
    <div tal:replace="structure view/actionsPortlet" />
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <h1>Bounties for
    <span tal:replace="context/browsername">Context</span>
  </h1>

  <p class="documentDescription">These are the bounties that are related to
  <span tal:replace="context/browsername">Context</span>. This report
  includes bounties issued by, claimed by or reviewed by the person, as well
  as bounties to which <span tal:replace="context/browsername" /> has
  subscribed. Click on a column header to sort by that header.</p>

  <h3>Bounties Issued</h3>

    <p tal:condition="not: context/ownedBounties"><span
    tal:replace="context/browsername">Person browsername</span> has not
    issued any bounties through the Launchpad system. Anybody can issue a
    bounty using  PayPal to place the bounty funds in escrow until
    the work is done.</p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing rowNavigation"
           tal:condition="context/ownedBounties">
      <tr>
        <th>Date Created</th>
        <th>Title</th>
        <th>USD Value<sup>*</sup></th>
      </tr>
      <tr tal:repeat="bounty context/ownedBounties"
          tal:attributes="onclick
              string:window.location='/bounties/${bounty/name}/';">
        <td tal:content="python:bounty.datecreated.strftime('%d %b %y')">
          date
        </td>
        <td><b><span tal:replace="bounty/title/fmt:shorten/45">title</span>
            </b>
        </td>
        <td tal:content="bounty/usdvalue">usdvalue</td>
      </tr>
  </table>

  <h3>Bounties Claimed</h3>

  <p tal:condition="not: context/claimedBounties"><span
  tal:replace="context/browsername">Person browsername</span> has not
  claimed any bounties in the Launchpad system. You claim a bounty by
  registering for it, and submitting code for review. If that code is judged
  by the bounty reviewer to be the winning entry before the deadline for the
  bounty expires, then the bounty is awarded to you and payment will be
  made.</p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing rowNavigation"
           tal:condition="context/claimedBounties">
      <tr>
        <th>Date Created</th>
        <th>Title</th>
        <th>USD Value<sup>*</sup></th>
      </tr>
      <tr tal:repeat="bounty context/claimedBounties"
          tal:attributes="onclick
              string:window.location='/bounties/${bounty/name}/';">
        <td tal:content="python:bounty.datecreated.strftime('%d %b %y')">
          date
        </td>
        <td><b><span tal:replace="bounty/title/fmt:shorten/45">title</span>
            </b>
        </td>
        <td tal:content="bounty/usdvalue">usdvalue</td>
      </tr>
  </table>

  <h3>Bounties Reviewed:</h3>

  <p tal:condition="not: context/reviewerBounties"><span
  tal:replace="context/browsername">Person browsername</span> is not the
  reviewer of any Launchpad bounties. The reviewer is responsible for
  judging the quality of bounty submissions and determines the winner, if
  any, of a bounty.</p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing rowNavigation"
           tal:condition="context/reviewerBounties">
      <tr>
        <th>Date Created</th>
        <th>Title</th>
        <th>USD Value<sup>*</sup></th>
      </tr>
      <tr tal:repeat="bounty context/reviewerBounties"
          tal:attributes="onclick
              string:window.location='/bounties/${bounty/name}/';">
        <td tal:content="python:bounty.datecreated.strftime('%d %b %y')">
          date
        </td>
        <td><b><span tal:replace="bounty/title/fmt:shorten/45">title</span>
            </b>
        </td>
        <td tal:content="bounty/usdvalue">usdvalue</td>
      </tr>
  </table>

  <h3>Bounties Subscribed:</h3>

  <p tal:condition="not: context/subscribedBounties"><span
  tal:replace="context/browsername">Person browsername</span> has not
  subscribed to any bounties.</p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing rowNavigation"
           tal:condition="context/subscribedBounties">
      <tr>
        <th>Date Created</th>
        <th>Title</th>
        <th>USD Value<sup>*</sup></th>
      </tr>
      <tr tal:repeat="bounty context/subscribedBounties"
          tal:attributes="onclick
              string:window.location='/bounties/${bounty/name}/';">
        <td tal:content="python:bounty.datecreated.strftime('%d %b %y')">
          date
        </td>
        <td><b><span tal:replace="bounty/title/fmt:shorten/45">title</span>
            </b>
        </td>
        <td tal:content="bounty/usdvalue">usdvalue</td>
      </tr>
  </table>

  <p><sup>*</sup> A bounty may include contributions in several currencies,
  this is an estimate of the bounty value in US Dollars based on recent
  exchange rates.</p>

  <p>Click on a bounty for further information. You can subscribe to
  a bounty to receive email updates of changes in status of the bounty, or
  to have the bounty show up on your personalised Launchpad overview
  page.</p>

</div>

</body>
</html>
